HEADWORD: Parelectronomy
<hw>Par*e`lec*tron"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>electro-</ets> + Gr. <?/ law.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A condition of the muscles induced by
exposure to severe cold, in which the electrical action of the muscle is
reversed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

